Mouthparts.
Labrum (
Figure 10C
) hood-shaped, covered by numerous short needle-like setae. Mandible (
Figure 10D, E
) robust, molar process with undulated margin and setae on ‘‘lower margin’’, 
lacinia mobilis
well-developed, crenulated. Maxillule (
Figure 10F
) endite as long as palp, with nine apical spiniform setae (two of them fused together); palp with two pinnate setae, one longer than the other. Maxilla (
Figure 19G
) hemispherical, smooth.
